Chopping Down the Syntax Tree


If Noam Chomsky’s Visiting Martian would return to our planet to catch up on the latest developments in linguistics, they would undoubtedly be intrigued by a new species of language researchers: construction grammarians. Construction grammarians come in different shapes and sizes, but they all embrace the idea that all linguistic knowledge can be represented as form-meaning mappings called constructions, which completely changes the way in which we understand the language capacity of humans. Unfortunately,